  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Writing the New World: The Politics of Natural History in the Early Spanish Empire (2021), published by University of Florida Press. Sustainability & policy relevance (strength 0.6). 1153 downloads \u2014 actief gebruik.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Writing the New World: The Politics of Natural History in the Early Spanish Empire was published by University of Florida Press in 2021. Conceptually, the work connects to Politics, Modernity, Empire, Colonialism and Narrative.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">OpenAlex records 9 citations. Citations peaked in 2022 with 2 citing works. Notable citing venues include Citizenship Studies, Hist\u00f3ria da Historiografia International Journal of Theory and History of Historiography and Librosdelacorte es. Inferred role: Sustainability & policy relevance and Scholarly uptake.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">1153 recorded downloads via open-access infrastructure.  SDG alignment: Life in Land.</p>",
